# ===================================================================
# Python / AI / Jupyter Monorepo .gitignore
# ===================================================================

# --- Secrets ---
# Never, ever commit your secret API keys or credentials.
# The double asterisk (**) ensures this works in any subdirectory.
**/.env

# --- Python Virtual Environments ---
# These are large, OS-specific, and can be recreated from requirements.txt
**/venv/
**/.venv/
**/env/
**/.env/

# --- Python Cache & Compiled Files ---
# These are generated by the Python interpreter and are not needed.
**/.pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd
**/build/
**/develop-eggs/
**/dist/
**/*.egg-info/
**/*.egg

# --- Jupyter Notebook Checkpoints ---
# These are automatic backups created by Jupyter and just add clutter.
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- IDE & Editor Configuration ---
# These files are specific to your local editor setup (VSCode, PyCharm, etc.)
# and should not be shared with collaborators.
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/

# --- Operating System Files ---
# Junk files created by macOS, Windows, and Linux.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
._*

# --- Optional: Generated Output Files ---
# It's good practice to not commit files that are generated by your code.
# You can uncomment these lines if you want to ignore them.
#
# *.png
# *.jpg
# *.jpeg
# *.gif
# *.svg
# *.csv
# *.db
# *.sqlite
# *.sqlite3
# *.html
# *.pdf